caption.p: Nyquist plot from electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) data of the tested alloys for LIBs ( a) and SIBs ( b). EIS data analyzed by fitting to an equivalent electrical circuit scheme (inset) in which R1 is the electrolyte solution resistance, R2 is the charge transfer resistance, CPE1 is the double-layer capacitance, and Wo1 is related to the diffusion-controlled Warburg impedance.
